    type:"misfortune",badge:"⚑ Imprisoned / Institutionalised Without Sentencing",
    summary:"Paul Pantone developed GEET (Global Environmental Energy Technology) — a self-generating plasma reformer that routes hot exhaust gases in counter-current contact with incoming fuel through a magnetic resonance rod, converting almost any liquid hydrocarbon — or reportedly crude oil, water, coffee, even urine — into a burnable synthetic gas. The claimed mechanism draws the incoming fuel into a near-plasma state, maximising molecular energy extraction. He received US Patent 5,794,601 in 1998. Engineers who attended his workshops went on to work at Los Alamos National Laboratory on plasma-assisted combustion research documenting mechanisms described as directly comparable to GEET's claimed operation. After refusing to sell his patents to interested buyers, he was charged with securities fraud in Utah in 2003 and entered a guilty plea to two counts in 2004. As sentencing approached in 2005, he was declared mentally incompetent and remanded without sentencing to the Utah State Hospital in Provo for nearly four years. Photographs from his hospitalisation showed dramatic physical deterioration. He was released in May 2009. He died in December 2015.",
    off:["Convicted: two counts securities fraud, guilty plea, 2004. Held at Utah State Hospital in Provo without sentencing, 2005–2009, released May 2009 without further criminal proceedings. Utah prosecutors described his engine claims as 'pure unadulterated nonsense.' Death: long illness, December 2015. US Patent 5,794,601 is on public record. The GEET device has been widely replicated in simplified form by engineers and hobbyists with varying results; no controlled independent scientific validation of over-unity output has been published."],
