    role:"Financier · Nobel laureate gatherer · 'Confronting Gravity' conference · ZPE / quantum vacuum funder",
    type:"network",badge:"🕸 Intelligence Network / Died in Custody",
    summary:"Jeffrey Epstein was not an energy inventor. He was something potentially more significant to this timeline: the man who systematically cultivated, funded, and concentrated relationships with the world's leading physicists working on gravity modification, zero-point energy, the quantum vacuum, and consciousness. His 2006 'Confronting Gravity' conference, held at a luxury hotel on St. Thomas with a boat trip to his private island Little St. James included, gathered Stephen Hawking, Nobel laureates Gerardus 't Hooft, David Gross, Frank Wilczek, and Kip Thorne, plus Alan Guth (MIT), Lisa Randall (Harvard), Barry Barish (LIGO), and Maria Spiropulu (CERN) — specifically to 'define gravity' and explore the physics of 'empty space.' He was arrested on federal sex trafficking charges in July 2019 and died in his cell at Metropolitan Correctional Center, Manhattan, on August 10, 2019, the night before proceedings that would have required him to identify his associates. The official cause was suicide by hanging. Independent forensic pathologist Michael Baden — hired by his brother — observed the autopsy and identified three neck fractures and stated his opinion was strangulation pressure rather than hanging.",
    off:["Death ruled suicide by hanging, NYC Chief Medical Examiner Barbara Sampson. Independent forensic pathologist Michael Baden disputes this finding, citing three neck fractures (hyoid bone and both sides of thyroid cartilage) as inconsistent with his 40+ year experience of jail suicides. Some physicians dispute Baden's interpretation, noting that multiple neck fractures can occur in hangings of older individuals. Two prison guards assigned to Epstein were indicted for falsifying records — charges later dropped. AG Barr described his death as 'a perfect storm of screw-ups.' FBI investigation found serious irregularities at the jail but brought no charges. No energy-suppression connection to his death has been alleged by any official body."],
