    role:"NASA Lead Electrostatics Scientist · Kennedy Space Center · Exodus Force · Townsend Brown vindicated",
    type:"aerospace",badge:"🛸 Active — 2,000+ Vacuum Tests · Patent Filed 2019",
    summary:"Dr. Charles 'Charlie' Buhler is NASA's subject matter expert on electrostatics: the founder of NASA's Electrostatics and Surface Physics Laboratory at Kennedy Space Center, the incoming president of the Electrostatic Society of America, and a veteran of the Shuttle, ISS, Hubble, and Lunar programs. Outside NASA, he co-founded Exodus Propulsion Technologies and claims to have discovered what he calls the 'Exodus Force': a new, fundamental force arising from electrostatic asymmetry that produces measurable propellantless thrust in vacuum — thrust that persists after the external power is switched off because charge trapped in the dielectric maintains the internal field. Over 2,000 vacuum chamber experiments. In 2023, the device produced enough thrust to counteract the gravitational force on its own propellant mass. He explicitly describes his work as a vindication of Thomas Townsend Brown, whose identical research was classified in 1956. His colleague Andrew Aurigema arrived at the same result independently, working from within the Townsend Brown electrogravitics literature.",
    off:["Not suppressed — active private company, Exodus Propulsion Technologies (Florida). Patent filed 2019: confirmed. Independent replication under controlled third-party laboratory conditions: pending as of 2026. Peer-reviewed publication of full test protocols and uncertainty budgets: pending. Mainstream physicists compare it to the EmDrive — initially promising, ultimately debunked after rigorous independent testing — and await independent verification. Buhler himself acknowledges the need for independent replication and has invited other laboratories to build and test. The 2,000+ experiments claim comes from his own APEC presentation slides; the count has not been independently audited."],
    connections:["Thomas Townsend Brown: Buhler explicitly names Brown as his predecessor; Aurigema worked from Brown's literature independently; the 1956 Aviation Studies reports describing Brown's effect are cited as the precedent Buhler is resolving.","Harold 'Sonny' White: both are NASA-credentialed physicists working on vacuum-level energy effects outside of their NASA roles; both are attempting to commercially develop technologies that mainstream physics does not yet accept."],
