    summary:"Dr. Harold G. 'Sonny' White spent 20 years at NASA's Johnson Space Center leading the Advanced Propulsion Team — the team responsible for the most serious institutional investigation of warp drives, the Alcubierre metric, and the physics of the quantum vacuum. He received the NASA Exceptional Achievement Medal. He has now built a chip — roughly the size of a pinky nail — that produces measurable, continuous electrical output of 1.5 volts at 25 microamps with no battery, no external power source, and no moving parts. The energy comes from the quantum vacuum via engineered Casimir cavities: nanoscale structures with strategically placed antennas and pillars that interact with the quantum field, causing a preferential flow of electrons analogous to how a solar panel captures photon energy — but drawing on virtual photons from the vacuum rather than real photons from the Sun. His paper, 'Emergent quantization from a dynamic vacuum,' is published in Physical Review Research (2026). DARPA is funding the research. He appeared on the Joe Rogan Experience (episode 2318) to discuss both the power chip and its warp drive implications.",
    off:["Not suppressed — active company (Casimir Inc.) with DARPA funding and peer-reviewed publication confirmed. Physical Review Research paper: 'Emergent quantization from a dynamic vacuum,' published 2026. Power output: 1.5V at 25µA = ~37.5 microwatts from a pinky-nail chip. Independent replication: pending. Thermodynamic debate ongoing — whether Casimir-cavity energy extraction can produce net useful work above the energy cost of chip fabrication is legitimately contested. The current output is minuscule but White compares it to the first transistor. DARPA funding confirmed in his own conference presentations; the specific programme and budget are not public."],
    quote:"\"What starts as a drop may become a flood of energy.\" — Harold 'Sonny' White",
    connections:["The Casimir Effect (1948): White's chip is the direct practical demonstration of what the Casimir entry establishes as theoretically real — energy extraction from the quantum vacuum.","Thomas Townsend Brown / Charles Buhler: all three working on the same fundamental question through different mechanisms — can electromagnetic effects in near-vacuum conditions produce useful propulsive or energetic output?"],
