    summary:"Anthony 'Tony' Chavez, 78, was last seen leaving his home on 37th Street in Los Alamos on foot on May 4, 2025. He was reported missing May 8. His wallet, keys, and cigarettes were left on the table. He carried no cell phone. A LANL institutional profile — surfaced by The Grounded (April 2026) — identifies him as an R&D engineer in Engineering, Operations, and Physics who worked at the laboratory for more than 25 years, including at DARHT. DARHT — the Dual Axis Radiographic Hydrodynamic Test Facility — uses powerful electron beam accelerators to generate X-ray pulses capable of imaging the implosion dynamics of nuclear weapons components in the microseconds of a hydronuclear experiment. It is central to the US stockpile stewardship programme. Detective Ladislas Szabo: 'There was no evidence of a scuffle. There was no blood. There was nothing. It was just like he left.' He has not been found.",
