    type:"misfortune",badge:"⚑ Missing — DOE Nuclear Weapons Complex",
    summary:"Steven Garcia, approximately 47–48, was last seen on August 28, 2025, leaving his home on Cattail Court SW, Albuquerque, on foot — wearing a green camouflage shirt and shorts and reportedly carrying a handgun — without his phone, keys, or wallet. New Mexico DPS maintains an open missing-person entry. Press citing an anonymous source describes him as a contractor at the Kansas City National Security Campus (KCNSC) in a property or asset oversight role. KCNSC is a Honeywell Federal Manufacturing & Technologies facility that manufactures the majority of non-nuclear components for US nuclear weapons — mechanical, electrical, and electronic parts that enable the warhead to function without themselves being fissile. A high-level asset oversight role at KCNSC would provide broad knowledge of nuclear weapons system architecture and component supply chains. His disappearance is widely cited in cluster coverage as the tenth named case in the 2023–26 series. Albuquerque Police noted publicly that he 'may be a danger to himself'; a source cited in press reporting disputed mental-health explanations.",
